## Introduction

R Markdown is a powerful tool that allows users to combine narrative text, executable R code, and results into a single document. This approach helps create reports that are clear, reproducible, and easy to share.

## What Is R Markdown?

R Markdown uses simple Markdown syntax for formatting text while allowing R code to be embedded directly into the document. When the document is compiled, the R code is executed and the results are included automatically in the final output. This makes R Markdown especially useful for data analysis and reporting.

## Math in R Markdown

R Markdown supports LaTeX-style math expressions.

